  <summary date="2015-07-09T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Bring Jobs Home Act

Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) grant business taxpayers a&#160;tax credit for up to 20% of insourcing expenses incurred for eliminating a&#160;business located outside the United States and&#160; relocating it within the United States, and (2) deny a tax deduction for outsourcing expenses incurred in relocating a U.S. business outside the United States. Requires an increase in the taxpayer's employment of full-time employees&#160;in the United States in order to claim the tax credit for insourcing expenses.</summary>
